						               													<description>How to play:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Make sure each couple has an answer board, one dry erase marker, and three Off Script tokens to share.&amp;#10;     The game is played in rounds. For the first round, each couple will answer an &amp;quot;Ask Her question Ladies first&amp;#10;     Choose a couple to go first&amp;#10;     The couple who goes first will roll the die to see which category question to answer from the &amp;quot;Ask Her&amp;quot; card.&amp;#10;     The couple reads the designated question aloud, along with the multiple choice answers&amp;#10;     Each husband writes the answer he believes his wife will choose (A, B, C, D. or E) on his answer board. The couples will take tums revealing their answers by each wife announcing her answer verbally-followed by her husband presenting his written answer to the group.&amp;#10;     Matching answers earn 1 point, or 2 points with a 2x roll, or 3 points when an Off Script token is used.&amp;#10;     The couple to the left rolls next!&amp;#10;     On to round two.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;                    &amp;#10;                &amp;#10;            &amp;#10;        &amp;#10;    &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Couples should not talk when being asked a question or while writing their answers, and they should be certain written answers cannot be seen by their spouse until it is time to reveal their answers. Have fun!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Off Script-After hearing the question, but before answering it, the couple has the option of choosing to use one of their three &amp;quot;Off Script&amp;quot; tokens to triple their point potential for that turn by selecting &amp;quot;E.&amp;quot; A matching answer is worth 3 points&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Wild Card - The couple who rolls the Wild Card chooses the category for the table for that round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Double points-All correct answers will be worth 2 points intead of 1, and the couple rolls again to determine the category. (If the Wild Card is rolled again, they may choose the category, and if they roll the 2x again, they may roll yet again until they get a category rall.)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3 Ways to Win! Be the: 1) 1st couple to score 3 points in each category or 2) couple with the most points after a designated number of rounds or 3) couple with the most points at the end of a designated time frame&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
